19920203000000000_58	The candidate with the highest number of votes in a constituency is elected even if he she receives a minority of the votes cast.	candid highest number vote constitu elect even receiv minor vote cast
19920203000000000_59	If no candidate wins more than 50 per cent of the votes the second choices appearing on the ballot for the candidate with the lowest umber of votes are re allocated until one candidate wins a majority of votes List system.	candid win per cent vote second choic appear ballot candid lowest umber vote alloc one candid win joriti vote list system
19920203000000000_60	Voters vote for party lists of candidates in multi member constituencies.	voter vote parti list candid multi member constitu
19920203000000000_61	Seats are divided between the parties in proportion to the vote gained in the constituency and allocated to candidates from the top of the list working down.	seat divid parti proport vote gain constitu alloc candid top list work
19920203000000000_62	Multi member constituencies with voters numbering candidates in order of preference.	multi member constitu voter number candid order prefer
19920203000000000_63	Complex formula elects candidates receiving more than a set quota of votes.	complex formula elect candid receiv set quota vote
19920203000000000_64	Second and subsequent preferences on votes in excess of the quota and those with the lowest numbers of first preferences are redistributed until enough candidates reach the quota.	second subsequ prefer vote excess quota lowest number first prefer redistribut enough candid reach quota
